This paper is about compressing deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper deals with neural networks and their optimization. The second most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the paper uses the ImageNet dataset to evaluate the performance of the compression method. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as neural networks are a key component of AI systems. The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper deals with optimizing neural networks. The fifth likely category is cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), as the paper discusses the deployment of neural networks on embedded systems with limited hardware resources.
